# How to use ikiwiki with git

## Get the wiki sources

First, you need you ssh key to be accepted. Please send your ssh public key
to <goneri@rulezlan.org>. Once, this step is done, you can clone the
wiki:

    git clone wiki@wiki.fusioninventory.org:wiki.git

## Hack

    vi foo.mdwn
    git commit -m "my awesome changes" foo.mdwn

## Push

    git push

# There is various way to convery a mdwn (Markdown) file to HTML.

For example, with pandoc:

    pandoc -f markdown -t html5 foo.mdwn > foo.html5
